## Confidence signals

These are informational. The ranking above is always emitted;
treat the signals as inputs when deciding how much to trust it.

- **Confidence gap**: {{ confidence_gap }} of max — gap between the
  top answer and the runner-up as a fraction of the maximum
  possible weighted score. Higher is more decisive.
- **Intransitivity cycles**: {{ intransitivity_cycles }} — directed
  3-cycles in the pair-win graph (e.g. A>B, B>C, C>A). >0 means
  the compares disagree about a strict order; the ranking falls
  back to averaged scores so it is still well-defined, but the
  reader should weigh the cycle when reading the verdict.
- **Rejected judgments**: {{ rejected_judgments_count }} — compare
  outputs excluded from aggregation due to missing evidence on
  one or more dimensions. Defense in depth on top of the
  compare schema's evidence enforcement.

