## How to read this

The ranking aggregates three pair-wise comparisons against a
session-aware rubric. Compare agents assign each side a 1-5
score per dimension (1 = clearly worse, 3 = acceptable, 5 =
clearly better). For each answer, scores are averaged across
the pairs the answer appears in, then weighted by the rubric's
per-dimension weight. The sum across dimensions is the answer's
final score. The pair-wise `winner` field is informational and
used only for cycle detection — never for promotion gating.

